msgctxt "#32093"
msgid "HDR tone mapping for previews"
msgstr "HDR tone mapping for previews"

msgctxt "#32094"
msgid "Tone-map HDR and Dolby Vision sources to SDR when generating trickplay JPEGs so colours match normal playback (similar to Jellyfin). Only applies to HDR/DV files; SDR generation is unchanged. Significantly slower on 4K HEVC — often several times longer per file — and requires ffmpeg tonemap support. Leave off if Jellyfin already generates sidecars or generation time matters."
msgstr "Tone-map HDR and Dolby Vision sources to SDR when generating trickplay JPEGs so colours match normal playback (similar to Jellyfin). Only applies to HDR/DV files; SDR generation is unchanged. Significantly slower on 4K HEVC — often several times longer per file — and requires ffmpeg tonemap support. Leave off if Jellyfin already generates sidecars or generation time matters."

msgctxt "#32095"
msgid "HDR dovi_tool fallback"
msgstr "HDR dovi_tool fallback"

msgctxt "#32096"
msgid "When HDR tone mapping is on, run dovi_tool on the first seconds of HEVC if ffprobe finds no HDR signals. Slower; place dovi_tool in the add-on folder or on PATH. Use for stubborn Dolby Vision remuxes. Skipped for VFS stream paths. With fallback on, Run can offer to download dovi_tool into the add-on folder."
msgstr "When HDR tone mapping is on, run dovi_tool on the first seconds of HEVC if ffprobe finds no HDR signals. Slower; place dovi_tool in the add-on folder or on PATH. Use for stubborn Dolby Vision remuxes. Skipped for VFS stream paths. With fallback on, Run can offer to download dovi_tool into the add-on folder."

msgctxt "#32097"
msgid "Generator ffmpeg path"
msgstr "Generator ffmpeg path"

msgctxt "#32098"
msgid "Optional folder or ffmpeg binary for trickplay generation (needs zscale or libplacebo for HDR tone mapping). Leave empty to use /storage/.kodi/system/ffmpeg/ on Linux Kodi, or addon_data/service.trickplay/system/ffmpeg/ on Windows, when present; otherwise tools.ffmpeg-tools. When HDR tone mapping is on, Run can offer to download a pinned build (BtbN gpl-8.1 on Linux, Gyan full on Windows). Playback cropping still uses tools.ffmpeg-tools."
msgstr "Optional folder or ffmpeg binary for trickplay generation (needs zscale or libplacebo for HDR tone mapping). Leave empty to use /storage/.kodi/system/ffmpeg/ on Linux Kodi, or addon_data/service.trickplay/system/ffmpeg/ on Windows, when present; otherwise tools.ffmpeg-tools. When HDR tone mapping is on, Run can offer to download a pinned build (BtbN gpl-8.1 on Linux, Gyan full on Windows). Playback cropping still uses tools.ffmpeg-tools."

msgctxt "#32099"
msgid "HDR tone mapping needs a capable ffmpeg build. Download and install now?\n\nLinux: BtbN gpl-8.1 (zscale). Windows: Gyan full build (zscale + libplacebo for Dolby Vision via Vulkan).\n\nOn devices without Vulkan (e.g. CoreELEC), Profile 5 Dolby Vision uses dovi_tool instead of libplacebo.\n\nInstall location: %s"
msgstr "HDR tone mapping needs a capable ffmpeg build. Download and install now?\n\nLinux: BtbN gpl-8.1 (zscale). Windows: Gyan full build (zscale + libplacebo for Dolby Vision via Vulkan).\n\nOn devices without Vulkan (e.g. CoreELEC), Profile 5 Dolby Vision uses dovi_tool instead of libplacebo.\n\nInstall location: %s"

